box": [202.9, 307.5, 598.3, 319.9]}, {"text": "Table 2. Cardiac MRI indices in never-smoking and smoking patients with DCMP. p values < 0.05 are denoted", "bbox": [198.9, 330.6, 705.3, 346.5]}, {"text": "by a bold font. BSA = body surface area; EDV = end diastolic volume; LGE = late gadolinium enhancement;", "bbox": [198.9, 343.8, 688.5, 359.3]}, {"text": "LV = left ventricle; RV = right ventricle; multi-segment involvement (≥3 segments).", "bbox": [198.9, 356.6, 580.7, 372.1]}, {"text": "Adjusted for Clinical", "bbox": [446.3, 409.1, 524.1, 421.5]}, {"text": "Adjusted for Clinical variables variables + Medications", "bbox": [313.0, 418.7, 534.9, 431.1]}, {"text": "OR 95% CI p value OR 95% CI p value", "bbox": [313.0, 433.6, 574.4, 445.9]}, {"text": "Age (per years) 1.008 0.984–1.032 0.521 1.003 0.978–1.029 0.81", "bbox": [202.9, 448.7, 563.0, 460.8]}, {"text": "Male 1.011 0.412–2.477 0.981 1.244 0.482–3.211 1.244", "bbox": [202.9, 463.6, 567.3, 475.7]}, {"text": "LVEDV/BSA (per 1 mL/m2) 0.999 0.996–1.003 0.728 0.999 0.996–1.002 0.999", "bbox": [203.0, 478.4, 567.3, 490.5]}, {"text": "LVEF (per 1%) 0.954 0.924–0.985 0.004 0.953 0.920–0.987 0.008", "bbox": [202.9, 493.0, 568.0, 505.4]}, {"text": "Hypertension 1.533 0.755–3.115 0.237 1.55 0.748–3.215 0.239", "bbox": [202.9, 508.2, 567.3, 520.2]}, {"text": "Diabetes 0.79 0.380–1.646 0.53 0.792 0.364–1.725 0.557", "bbox": [202.9, 523.0, 567.3, 535.1]}, {"text": "Alcohol 2.751 1.062–7.125 0.037 3.239 1.196–8.774 0.021", "bbox": [203.0, 537.6, 568.0, 550.0]}, {"text": "Smoking 3.124 1.211–8.061 0.018 3.694 1.396–9.775 0.008", "bbox": [203.0, 552.4, 568.0, 564.8]}, {"text": "Medication", "bbox": [203.0, 567.6, 243.8, 579.7]}, {"text": "  ACE inhibitor/ARB 0.837 0.230–3.052 0.788", "bbox": [203.0, 582.5, 567.3, 594.5]}, {"text": "  Beta blocker 1.093 0.480–2.491 0.832", "bbox": [203.0, 597.3, 567.3, 609.4]}, {"text": "  Loop diuretics 3.819 1.269–11.495 0.017", "bbox": [203.0, 612.2, 567.3, 624.3]}, {"text": "  Aldosterone antagonist 0.664 0.255–1.725 0.4", "bbox": [203.0, 627.1, 558.7, 639.1]}, {"text": "  Statin 0.881 0.430–1.803 0.728", "bbox": [203.0, 641.9, 567.3, 654.0]}, {"text": "  Amiodarone 1.681 0.321–8.803 0.539", "bbox": [203.0, 656.8, 567.4, 668.9]}, {"text": "Table 3. The effect of smoking on the LV-LGE (Multivariate analysis). p values < 0.05 are denoted by a bold", "bbox": [198.9, 679.5, 688.1, 695.5]}, {"text": "font. ACE = angiotensin-converting enzyme; ARB = angiotensin receptor blocker; BSA = body surface area;", "bbox": [198.9, 692.7, 690.0, 708.2]}, {"text": "LVEDV = left ventricular end diastolic volume; LVEF = left ventricular ejection fraction.", "bbox": [198.9, 705.5, 601.5, 721.0]}, {"text": "FVAs (Log Rank p = 0.002, Fig. 3-C). When considering most smokers were male (95.4%), male smokers also had", "bbox": [198.9, 759.4, 708.7, 774.9]}, {"text": "significantly more FVA events than male never-smokers (Log Rank p = 0.043, Fig. 3-D). In an analysis combining", "bbox": [198.9, 772.1, 708.9, 787.7]}, {"text": "an LGE and smoking, never-smokers without an LGE (−) had the lowest number of FVA events, and smokers", "bbox": [198.9, 784.9, 709.0, 800.4]}, {"text": "with an LGE (+) had the highest number of FVA events. Especially smokers without an LGE (−) had a higher", "bbox": [198.9, 797.7, 708.9, 813.2]}, {"text": "risk of FVAs than never-smokers with an LGE (+), and as a consequence, smoking had a greater association with", "bbox": [198.9, 810.5, 709.1, 826.0]}, {"text": "the occurrence of FVAs than the presence of an LGE (Fig. 4-A). Also, in an analysis of FVA + SCD, an LGE (+)", "bbox": [198.9, 823.3, 708.9, 838.8]}, {"text": "and smoking had consistent effects on ventricular arrhythmic events (Fig. 4-B). In a Cox regression multivar-", "bbox": [198.9, 836.0, 708.9, 851.6]}, {"text": "iate analysis, a young age (HR = 0.96, 95% CI 0.95–0.996, p = 0.028), low body mass index (BMI) (HR = 0.83,", "bbox": [198.9, 848.8, 708.9, 864.3]}, {"text": "95% CI 0.716–0.962, p = 0.014), increased LVEDV (HR = 1.004, 95% CI 1.001–1.006, p = 0.004), alcohol intake", "bbox": [198.9, 861.6, 708.9, 877.1]}, {"text": "(HR = 3.909, 95% CI 1.005–15.208, p = 0.049), and smoking (HR = 5.588, 95% CI 1.389–22.490, p = 0.015) were", "bbox": [198.9, 874.4, 708.9, 889.9]}, {"text": "associated with FVAs or SCD. Finally, a low BMI and diastolic BP including smoking were common predictors of", "bbox": [198.9, 887.2, 708.6, 902.7]}, {"text": "FVAs and FVA + SCD in patients with DCMP (Table 4), in addition, in the ROC curve analysis, the AUC area of", "bbox": [198.9, 899.9, 708.9, 915.5]}, {"text": "the FVA group including smoking was 0.822, and the AUC area in the FVA + SCD group was 0.787, respectively", "bbox": [198.9, 912.7, 708.9, 928.2]}, {"text": "(Supplement Fig. 1).", "bbox": [198.9, 925.5, 291.7, 941.0]}, {"text": "SCIEntIfIC REPORTS | (2018) 8:15609 | DOI:10.1038/s41598-018-34145-9 5", "bbox": [52.1, 964.7, 708.9, 979.9]}]}